---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Justin Rudisal"
  description="How this site handles your data. Short version: it collects very little and tracks nothing."
  ogImagePath="/og/privacy.png"
  canonicalPath="/privacy"
>
  <a slot="skip-link" href="#main-content" class="skip-to-content">
    Skip to main content
  </a>
  <Navbar slot="navbar" />

  <div class="min-h-screen bg-surface pt-24 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <a
        href="/"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-text-muted hover:text-accent transition-colors duration-200 text-sm mb-10 focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-accent focus-visible:outline-offset-2 rounded"
      >
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10.5 19.5L3 12m0 0l7.5-7.5M3 12h18" />
        </svg>
        Back to home
      </a>

      <header class="mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary leading-tight mb-4">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">
          Last updated May 3, 2026
        </p>
      </header>

      <hr class="border-surface-light/20 mb-10" />

      <div class="space-y-10 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          This is a personal portfolio and blog. It doesn't use tracking pixels, doesn't set cookies
          for analytics, and doesn't sell or share your data with anyone. Here's exactly what happens
          when you visit.
        </p>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Contact form</h2>
          <p>
            When you submit the contact form, your <strong class="text-text-primary">name</strong>,
            <strong class="text-text-primary">email address</strong>, and
            <strong class="text-text-primary">message</strong> are sent to me through
            <a href="https://www.emailjs.com/docs/legal/privacy-policy/" class="text-accent hover:text-text-primary transition-colors duration-200" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">EmailJS</a>.
            I use that information to reply to you and nothing else.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The form also uses
            <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" class="text-accent hover:text-text-primary transition-colors duration-200" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare Turnstile</a>
            to verify you're a real person. Turnstile doesn't track you across sites and doesn't use cookies.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            To prevent spam, the form stores a count of recent submissions in your browser's
            <strong class="text-text-primary">localStorage</strong>. This data never leaves your device and
            contains no personal information, just timestamps.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Newsletter</h2>
          <p>
            If you subscribe to the newsletter, your <strong class="text-text-primary">email address</strong>
            is sent to
            <a href="https://buttondown.com/legal/privacy" class="text-accent hover:text-text-primary transition-colors duration-200" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Buttondown</a>,
            which handles subscriptions and delivery. Every email includes an unsubscribe link.
            You can also unsubscribe by contacting me directly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Hosting and infrastructure</h2>
          <p>
            This site is hosted on
            <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" class="text-accent hover:text-text-primary transition-colors duration-200" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare Pages</a>.
            Cloudflare may collect standard server logs (IP address, browser type, pages requested)
            as part of operating their network. I don't have access to individual visitor logs.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Google Fonts</h2>
          <p>
            This site loads typefaces from Google Fonts. When a page loads, your browser connects to
            Google's servers to download the font files, which means
            <strong class="text-text-primary">your IP address is sent to Google</strong>.
            Google's font API is designed to limit the collection of information, but you can read
            <a href="https://developers.google.com/fonts/faq/privacy" class="text-accent hover:text-text-primary transition-colors duration-200" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's privacy FAQ</a>
            for the full details.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Analytics</h2>
          <p>
            This site uses
            <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/" class="text-accent hover:text-text-primary transition-colors duration-200" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare Web Analytics</a>
            to understand which pages get traffic, where visitors come from, and basic performance
            metrics. It collects aggregate, anonymous data including page views, referrers, country,
            device type, browser, and operating system.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Cloudflare Web Analytics <strong class="text-text-primary">does not use cookies</strong>,
            does not use localStorage, does not fingerprint visitors, and does not track individuals
            across sessions or sites. There is no way for me to identify who you are from the data
            it collects.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">What this site doesn't do</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-1">
            <li>No cookies (Turnstile and Cloudflare may set functional cookies, but I don't set any)</li>
            <li>No advertising</li>
            <li>No data sales or sharing with third parties for marketing</li>
            <li>No fingerprinting or cross-site tracking</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Your rights</h2>
          <p>
            If you want me to delete any data I have about you (contact form messages, newsletter
            subscription), just reach out through the
            <a href="/#contact" class="text-accent hover:text-text-primary transition-colors duration-200">contact form</a>
            or email me. I'll take care of it.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            If you're in the EU, you have rights under GDPR including access, correction, deletion,
            and portability of your personal data. If you're in California, you have similar rights
            under the CCPA. Either way, contact me and I'll help.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Third-party services</h2>
          <p>
            For complete details on how each service handles data, here are their privacy policies:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mt-3 ml-1">
            <li>
              <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" class="text-accent hover:text-text-primary transition-colors duration-200" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare</a>
              (hosting, CDN, Turnstile, Web Analytics)
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://www.emailjs.com/docs/legal/privacy-policy/" class="text-accent hover:text-text-primary transition-colors duration-200" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">EmailJS</a>
              (contact form delivery)
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://buttondown.com/legal/privacy" class="text-accent hover:text-text-primary transition-colors duration-200" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Buttondown</a>
              (newsletter)
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://developers.google.com/fonts/faq/privacy" class="text-accent hover:text-text-primary transition-colors duration-200" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Fonts</a>
              (typeface delivery)
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Changes</h2>
          <p>
            If this policy changes in a meaningful way, I'll update the date at the top of the page.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>
